<p>GDP growth: -0.1% GDP: $264bn (PPP: $210bn) Inflation: 2.3% Population: 5.4m GDP per head: $49,010 (PPP: $39,050)</p>

<p>The unwieldy six-party coalition that emerged from the mid-2011 election spans the entire political spectrum, and may founder over policy disputes. Despite its scope, the coalition excludes the third-placed True Finns, who will press a nationalist programme from the opposition benches, taking a determined stance, for instance, against bail-outs for troubled euro-zone partners. The administration will cut spending to narrow the fiscal gap, adding to the woes afflicting the euro zone and leading to a slight contraction in Finland's economy.</p>

